This patch enhances MLflow logging for production use with comprehensive metrics tracking.

ENHANCEMENTS:
1. Step-level logging in training loop (train loss, accuracy, LR, GPU metrics per batch)
2. Epoch-level summaries (comprehensive training/validation metrics)
3. HPO trial-level logging (nested runs for each trial with full params and metrics)
4. System metrics module (CPU, memory, GPU utilization, temperature)
5. Model registry support (register models with signatures, stages, tags)

FILES MODIFIED:
- src/psy_agents_noaug/training/train_loop.py
- src/psy_agents_noaug/hpo/optuna_runner.py
- src/psy_agents_noaug/utils/mlflow_utils.py

FILES CREATED:
- src/psy_agents_noaug/utils/system_metrics.py

REQUIRED DEPENDENCIES (add to pyproject.toml):
- psutil (for system metrics)
- pynvml (optional, for detailed GPU metrics)
- pandas (for HPO trial history export)

MLFLOW UI HIERARCHY:
Experiment
├── HPO_study_name (parent run)
│   ├── Metrics: best_val_f1_macro, total_trials, completed_trials, etc.
│   ├── Parameters: best_hpo/* (best hyperparameters)
│   ├── Artifacts: hpo_trials_history.csv, plots
│   └── Nested Runs:
│       ├── trial_0001
│       │   ├── Metrics: trial/val_f1_macro, train/loss_step, epoch/*, system/*
│       │   ├── Parameters: hpo/* (trial hyperparameters)
│       │   └── Artifacts: checkpoints, config
│       ├── trial_0002
│       └── ...
└── Regular Training Runs
    ├── Metrics: train/*, epoch/*, system/*, final/*
    ├── Parameters: model, training, data configs
    └── Artifacts: checkpoints, config.yaml

USAGE:
1. Training with system metrics:
   trainer = Trainer(..., log_system_metrics=True, system_metrics_interval=10)
   
2. Register model after training:
   from psy_agents_noaug.utils.mlflow_utils import register_model
   register_model(model, "criteria_model", sample_input, stage="Production")
   
3. HPO with nested runs:
   runner.optimize(..., mlflow_experiment_name="hpo_criteria")

BACKWARD COMPATIBILITY:
All changes are backward compatible. Existing code will work without modifications.
New features are opt-in via parameters.
